trans-unit.source: Supports a simple iteration over a <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: 간단한 반복을 지원 한 <xref href="System.Collections.Specialized.StringCollection"> </xref>합니다.

trans-unit.source: The `foreach` statement of the C# language (`for each` in Visual Basic) hides the complexity of the enumerators.
trans-unit.target: `foreach` C# 언어의 (`for each` Visual basic에서)은 열거자의 복잡성을 숨깁니다.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, using `foreach` is recommended, instead of directly manipulating the enumerator.
trans-unit.target: 따라서 사용 하 여 `foreach` 열거자를 직접 조작 하는 대신이 좋습니다.

trans-unit.source: Enumerators can be used to read the data in the collection, but they cannot be used to modify the underlying collection.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션의에서 데이터를 읽는 데 사용할 수 있지만 기본 컬렉션을 수정 하는 사용할 수 없습니다.

trans-unit.source: Initially, the enumerator is positioned before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 처음에 열거자는 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소 앞에 배치 됩니다.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> also brings the enumerator back to this position.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>또한이 위치로 복원 열거자를 가져옵니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: At this position, calling <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: 이 위치에서, 호출 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>예외를 throw 합니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: Therefore, you must call <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: 따라서 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> 의 값을 읽기 전에 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소로 열거자를</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 호출 해야 합니다.

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>될 때까지 동일한 개체를 반환 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>또는 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>호출 됩니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A></xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> sets <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> to the next element.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>설정 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>를 다음 요소로.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A></xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: 경우 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>전달 컬렉션의 마지막 요소 뒤에 열거자는 컬렉션의 끝에 배치 되 고 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>반환 `false`.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> also return `false`.
trans-unit.target: 열거자가 있는 경우이 위치에 대 한 후속 호출에서 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>반환할 수도 `false`.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the last call to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, calling <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> throws an exception.
trans-unit.target: 마지막으로 호출 하는 경우 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>반환 `false`호출, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>예외를 throw 합니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: To set <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> to the first element of the collection again, you can call <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> followed by <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>다시, 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소를 호출할 수 있습니다 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>그 뒤 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> 설정 하려면

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션이 변경 되지으로 유효한 상태를 유지 합니다.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: 예: 추가, 수정 또는 요소를 삭제, 열거자가 복구할 수 없게 무효화 및 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> throw</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> 또는</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 을 다음에 호출할 컬렉션 변경 될 경우

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the element that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: 사이 컬렉션이 수정 되는 경우 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>및 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>열거자가 이미 무효로 되 었 하는 경우에 설정 하는 요소를 반환 합니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The enumerator does not have exclusive access to the collection; therefore, enumerating through a collection is intrinsically not a thread-safe procedure.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션에 배타적으로 액세스가 없습니다. 따라서 컬렉션을 열거 것은 본질적으로 스레드로부터 안전한 프로시저가 아닙니다.

trans-unit.source: Even when a collection is synchronized, other threads can still modify the collection, which causes the enumerator to throw an exception.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션이 동기화 되어 있을 때 다른 스레드에서 수 수정할 열거자에서 예외가 발생 하는 컬렉션입니다.

trans-unit.source: To guarantee thread safety during enumeration, you can either lock the collection during the entire enumeration or catch the exceptions resulting from changes made by other threads.
trans-unit.target: 열거 동안 스레드 보안을 보장 하려면 전체 열거 동안 컬렉션을 잠글 하거나 다른 스레드에서 변경 된 내용으로 인해 발생 한 예외를 catch 합니다.

trans-unit.source: Gets the current element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션의 현재 요소를 가져옵니다.

trans-unit.source: After an enumerator is created or after a <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> must be called to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of Current; otherwise, Current is undefined.
trans-unit.target: 열거자를 만들거나는 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>호출 되 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>호출 하 여 열거자의 현재; 값을 읽기 전에 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소를 현재 그렇지 않으면 정의 되지 않습니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: Current also throws an exception if the last call to <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> returned `false`, which indicates the end of the collection.
trans-unit.target: 현재 예외를 throw 마지막으로 호출 하는 경우 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>반환 `false`, 컬렉션의 끝을 나타내는.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: Current does not move the position of the enumerator, and consecutive calls to Current return the same object until either <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 현재가 열거자의 위치를 이동 하지 않으며 현재 연속 해 서 호출 될 때까지 동일한 개체를 반환 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>또는 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>호출 됩니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> </xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션이 변경 되지으로 유효한 상태를 유지 합니다.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: 예: 추가, 수정 또는 요소를 삭제, 열거자가 복구할 수 없게 무효화 및 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> throw</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 또는</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 을 다음에 호출할 컬렉션 변경 될 경우

trans-unit.source: If the collection is modified between <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> and <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> returns the element that it is set to, even if the enumerator is already invalidated.
trans-unit.target: 사이 컬렉션이 수정 되는 경우 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>및 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>열거자가 이미 무효로 되 었 하는 경우에 설정 하는 요소를 반환 합니다.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: The current element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션의 현재 요소입니다.

trans-unit.source: The enumerator is positioned before the first element of the collection or after the last element.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션의 또는 마지막 요소 뒤의 첫 번째 요소 앞에 배치 됩니다.

trans-unit.source: Advances the enumerator to the next element of the collection.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션의 다음 요소로 이동 합니다.

trans-unit.source: After an enumerator is created or after a <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called, an enumerator is positioned before the first element of the collection, and the first call to MoveNext moves the enumerator over the first element of the collection.
trans-unit.target: 열거자를 만든 후 또는 이후에 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>가 호출 되는 열거자를 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소 앞에 배치 됩니다 고, movenext 첫 번째 호출 열거자를 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소로 이동 합니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: If MoveNext passes the end of the collection, the enumerator is positioned after the last element in the collection and MoveNext returns `false`.
trans-unit.target: MoveNext 컬렉션의 끝을 통과 열거자는 컬렉션의 마지막 요소 뒤에 배치 되 고 MoveNext 반환 `false`합니다.

trans-unit.source: When the enumerator is at this position, subsequent calls to MoveNext also return `false` until <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A> is called.
trans-unit.target: 이 위치에 열거자는 복구 불가능, 이후에 MoveNext 호출 또한 반환 `false` 될 때까지 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>호출 됩니다.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Reset%2A>

trans-unit.source: An enumerator remains valid as long as the collection remains unchanged.
trans-unit.target: 열거자는 컬렉션이 변경 되지으로 유효한 상태를 유지 합니다.

trans-unit.source: If changes are made to the collection, such as adding, modifying, or deleting elements, the enumerator is irrecoverably invalidated and the next call to <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> or <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> throws an <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.
trans-unit.target: 예: 추가, 수정 또는 요소를 삭제, 열거자가 복구할 수 없게 무효화 및 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> <xref:System.InvalidOperationException>.</xref:System.InvalidOperationException> throw</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Reset%2A> 또는</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 을 다음에 호출할 컬렉션 변경 될 경우

trans-unit.target: 사이 컬렉션이 수정 되는 경우 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>및 <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>, <xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A>열거자가 이미 무효로 되 었 하는 경우에 설정 하는 요소를 반환 합니다.</xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.Current%2A> </xref:System.Collections.IEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if the enumerator was successfully advanced to the next element; <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref> if the enumerator has passed the end of the collection.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>열거자를 다음 요소로 이동 성공 <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref> 열거자가 컬렉션의 끝을 통과 하는 경우.

trans-unit.source: The collection was modified after the enumerator was created.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션은 열거자를 만든 후 수정 되었습니다.

trans-unit.source: Sets the enumerator to its initial position, which is before the first element in the collection.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소 앞의 초기 위치에 열거자를 설정 합니다.

trans-unit.source: Reset moves the enumerator to the beginning of the collection, before the first element.
trans-unit.target: 첫 번째 요소 앞의 컬렉션의 시작 부분에는 열거자를 이동 하는 다시 설정 합니다.

trans-unit.source: After Reset, <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> must be called to advance the enumerator to the first element of the collection before reading the value of <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A>호출 하 여 <xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A>.</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.Current%2A> 의 값을 읽기 전에 컬렉션의 첫 번째 요소로 열거자를 이동 해야</xref:System.Collections.Specialized.StringEnumerator.MoveNext%2A> 하는 다시 설정한 후

trans-unit.source: The collection was modified after the enumerator was created.
trans-unit.target: 컬렉션은 열거자를 만든 후 수정 되었습니다.
